{"id":"v17-required-plan-001","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Give a three-step plan to tune a noisy formatter. Include benign samples, Compare, and clean output.","target_response":"1. Add benign samples that should remain unchanged.\n2. Compare failed rows by rule.\n3. Tighten only checks that block clean output.","verifier":{"required_terms":["benign samples","Compare","clean output"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":230},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-required-plan-002","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Write three numbered steps for reducing false positives in a parser. Include benign cases, Compare, and passing rows.","target_response":"1. Collect benign cases that should pass.\n2. Compare each miss by parser rule.\n3. Update the narrow rule and rerun passing rows.","verifier":{"required_terms":["benign cases","Compare","passing rows"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":230},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-required-plan-003","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Provide a three-step plan for checking regression fixes. Include sample set, Compare, and accepted rows.","target_response":"1. Build a sample set with known expected outcomes.\n2. Compare old and new failures.\n3. Keep the fix only if accepted rows still pass.","verifier":{"required_terms":["sample set","Compare","accepted rows"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":230},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-required-plan-004","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Make a numbered three-step plan for improving a brief-answer checker. Include short answers, Compare, and valid rows.","target_response":"1. Add short answers that should pass.\n2. Compare rejected rows by label.\n3. Relax only the rule that blocks valid rows.","verifier":{"required_terms":["short answers","Compare","valid rows"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":220},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-required-plan-005","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Give three numbered steps for repairing a required-word test. Include missing terms, Compare, and target phrase.","target_response":"1. List missing terms from each failed row.\n2. Compare them with the target phrase.\n3. Add examples that preserve the target phrase.","verifier":{"required_terms":["missing terms","Compare","target phrase"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":230},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-required-plan-006","category":"v17_capability_required_terms_plan","prompt":"Draft a three-step plan for reducing stale comparison mistakes. Include current baseline, Compare, and held-out rows.","target_response":"1. Record the current baseline result.\n2. Compare fixed and regressed cases.\n3. Test again on held-out rows.","verifier":{"required_terms":["current baseline","Compare","held-out rows"],"required_regex":["(?m)^1\\. ","(?m)^2\\. ","(?m)^3\\. "],"max_chars":220},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:required_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-one-line-001","category":"v17_capability_one_line_no_list","prompt":"In one sentence, state the next repair step after old eval failures. Include failure labels, new training rows, and fresh comparison set. Do not use a list.","target_response":"Use failure labels to write new training rows, then check the result on a fresh comparison set.","verifier":{"required_terms":["failure labels","new training rows","fresh comparison set"],"forbidden_regex":["\\n","(?m)^\\s*[-*]","(?m)^\\s*\\d+\\."],"max_chars":150},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:forbidden_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-one-line-002","category":"v17_capability_one_line_no_list","prompt":"Give one line about how to handle a format miss. Include exact output, shorter answer, and rerun check. No bullets.","target_response":"Repair toward exact output with a shorter answer, then run the rerun check.","verifier":{"required_terms":["exact output","shorter answer","rerun check"],"forbidden_regex":["\\n","(?m)^\\s*[-*]","(?m)^\\s*\\d+\\."],"max_chars":130},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:forbidden_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
{"id":"v17-one-line-003","category":"v17_capability_one_line_no_list","prompt":"Answer in one sentence: what should follow a regression found in a planning row? Include regressed case, repair seed, and baseline compare.","target_response":"Use the regressed case to shape a repair seed, then run a baseline compare.","verifier":{"required_terms":["regressed case","repair seed","baseline compare"],"forbidden_regex":["\\n","(?m)^\\s*[-*]","(?m)^\\s*\\d+\\."],"max_chars":140},"source":"codex_v16_v11_failure_label_analysis","split":"train_seed","evidence_level":"train_seed_not_capability_evidence","clean_claim_eligible":false,"verifier_labels":["verifier:required_terms","verifier:forbidden_regex","verifier:max_chars"]}
